---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
---

<ToolLayout
  title="AI Sentiment Analyzer"
  description="Analyze the sentiment and emotion of any text using AI. Detect positive, negative, or neutral tone instantly. Free, private, runs in your browser."
  isAI={true}
>
  <div id="sentiment-app">
    <div id="sa-status" class="mb-4 p-3 bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-lg text-sm text-yellow-700">
      Click "Analyze" to load the AI model (first time may take 15-30 seconds to download).
    </div>

    <textarea
      id="sa-input"
      rows="6"
      placeholder="Enter the text you want to analyze for sentiment..."
      class="w-full border border-gray-300 rounded-lg p-4 text-base resize-y focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-indigo-500 focus:border-transparent"
    ></textarea>

    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mt-4">
      <button id="sa-run" class="bg-indigo-600 text-white px-6 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm font-medium hover:bg-indigo-700 transition-colors disabled:opacity-50 disabled:cursor-not-allowed">
        Analyze Sentiment
      </button>
      <button id="sa-clear" class="bg-gray-200 text-gray-700 px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg text-sm hover:bg-gray-300 transition-colors">
        Clear
      </button>
      <div id="sa-spinner" class="hidden">
        <svg class="animate-spin h-5 w-5 text-indigo-600" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <circle class="opacity-25" cx="12" cy="12" r="10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="4"></circle>
          <path class="opacity-75" fill="currentColor" d="M4 12a8 8 0 018-8V0C5.373 0 0 5.373 0 12h4zm2 5.291A7.962 7.962 0 014 12H0c0 3.042 1.135 5.824 3 7.938l3-2.647z"></path>
        </svg>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="sa-result" class="mt-6 hidden">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div id="sa-main-result" class="p-6 rounded-xl text-center">
          <div id="sa-emoji" class="text-6xl mb-3"></div>
          <div id="sa-label" class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2"></div>
          <div id="sa-score" class="text-sm text-gray-500"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <h3 class="font-semibold">Breakdown</h3>
          <div id="sa-bars"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- SEO Content -->
  <div class="mt-12 prose prose-sm max-w-none">
    <h2>Free AI Sentiment Analysis Tool</h2>
    <p>Analyze the sentiment of any text using AI. Our tool detects whether text is positive, negative, or neutral, with a confidence score. Perfect for analyzing customer reviews, social media posts, emails, and more.</p>

    <h3>How does Sentiment Analysis work?</h3>
    <p>This tool uses a pre-trained natural language processing (NLP) model that runs entirely in your browser using Transformers.js. The model analyzes the emotional tone and context of your text to determine its sentiment.</p>

    <h3>Use Cases</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Analyzing customer reviews and feedback</li>
      <li>Monitoring social media sentiment</li>
      <li>Evaluating email tone before sending</li>
      <li>Content quality assessment</li>
      <li>Market research and opinion mining</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">How to Use the AI Sentiment Analyzer</h2>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-3 text-gray-600">
      <li><strong>Enter your text</strong> — Paste or type the text you want to analyze into the input box. This can be a review, email, tweet, or any other text up to 512 characters.</li>
      <li><strong>Click "Analyze Sentiment"</strong> — The AI model will load on first use (this takes 15-30 seconds). Subsequent analyses are instant.</li>
      <li><strong>Review the results</strong> — See whether your text is classified as Positive or Negative, along with a confidence percentage.</li>
      <li><strong>Check the breakdown</strong> — View the full score distribution across sentiment categories to understand the nuance of the analysis.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <div class="mt-12 space-y-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Is this sentiment analysis tool free to use?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">Yes, the AI Sentiment Analyzer is completely free with no usage limits. The AI model runs directly in your browser, so there are no server costs or API fees involved.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Is my text data sent to any server?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">No. The sentiment analysis model is downloaded once to your browser and all processing happens locally on your device. Your text never leaves your computer, making this tool safe for confidential content.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">How accurate is AI sentiment analysis?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">This tool uses a DistilBERT model fine-tuned on the SST-2 dataset, which achieves over 90% accuracy on standard benchmarks. It works best on clearly opinionated text like reviews and social media posts. Sarcasm and highly nuanced text may be more challenging.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">What languages does the sentiment analyzer support?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">The current model is optimized for English text. While it may produce results for other languages, accuracy will be significantly lower. We recommend using English text for the most reliable analysis.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
      <summary class="font-semibold cursor-pointer">Can I analyze long documents or bulk text?</summary>
      <p class="mt-3 text-gray-600 text-sm">The tool processes up to 512 characters at a time, which covers most reviews, tweets, and short paragraphs. For longer documents, we recommend breaking the text into smaller sections and analyzing each one individually.</p>
    </details>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>

<script type="module">
  import { pipeline } from 'https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@huggingface/transformers@3.5.1';

  let classifier = null;
  const statusEl = document.getElementById('sa-status');
  const inputEl = document.getElementById('sa-input');
  const runBtn = document.getElementById('sa-run');
  const spinner = document.getElementById('sa-spinner');
  const resultEl = document.getElementById('sa-result');

  async function loadModel() {
    statusEl.className = 'mb-4 p-3 bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg text-sm text-blue-700';
    statusEl.textContent = 'Loading AI model...';
    runBtn.disabled = true;
    spinner.classList.remove('hidden');

    try {
      classifier = await pipeline('sentiment-analysis', 'Xenova/distilbert-base-uncased-finetuned-sst-2-english', {
        dtype: 'q8',
      });
      statusEl.className = 'mb-4 p-3 bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg text-sm text-green-700';
      statusEl.textContent = 'AI model loaded! Ready to analyze.';
    } catch (err) {
      statusEl.className = 'mb-4 p-3 bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg text-sm text-red-700';
      statusEl.textContent = 'Failed to load model: ' + err.message;
    } finally {
      runBtn.disabled = false;
      spinner.classList.add('hidden');
    }
  }

  runBtn.addEventListener('click', async () => {
    const text = inputEl.value.trim();
    if (!text) {
      alert('Please enter some text to analyze.');
      return;
    }

    if (!classifier) {
      await loadModel();
      if (!classifier) return;
    }

    runBtn.disabled = true;
    spinner.classList.remove('hidden');

    try {
      const result = await classifier(text.slice(0, 512), { topk: null });

      const mainResult = result[0];
      const emojiMap = { POSITIVE: '😊', NEGATIVE: '😟', NEUTRAL: '😐' };
      const colorMap = {
        POSITIVE: 'bg-green-50 border border-green-200',
        NEGATIVE: 'bg-red-50 border border-red-200',
        NEUTRAL: 'bg-gray-50 border border-gray-200',
      };
      const barColorMap = {
        POSITIVE: 'bg-green-500',
        NEGATIVE: 'bg-red-500',
        NEUTRAL: 'bg-gray-500',
      };

      document.getElementById('sa-main-result').className =
        `p-6 rounded-xl text-center ${colorMap[mainResult.label] || colorMap.NEUTRAL}`;
      document.getElementById('sa-emoji').textContent = emojiMap[mainResult.label] || '🤔';
      document.getElementById('sa-label').textContent = mainResult.label;
      document.getElementById('sa-score').textContent = `Confidence: ${(mainResult.score * 100).toFixed(1)}%`;

      const barsHtml = result
        .sort((a, b) => b.score - a.score)
        .map(
          (r) => `
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="w-24 text-sm font-medium">${r.label}</span>
          <div class="flex-1 bg-gray-200 rounded-full h-4">
            <div class="${barColorMap[r.label] || 'bg-gray-500'} h-4 rounded-full transition-all" style="width: ${(r.score * 100).toFixed(1)}%"></div>
          </div>
          <span class="text-sm text-gray-600 w-16 text-right">${(r.score * 100).toFixed(1)}%</span>
        </div>
      `
        )
        .join('');

      document.getElementById('sa-bars').innerHTML = barsHtml;
      resultEl.classList.remove('hidden');

      statusEl.className = 'mb-4 p-3 bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-lg text-sm text-green-700';
      statusEl.textContent = 'Analysis complete!';
    } catch (err) {
      statusEl.className = 'mb-4 p-3 bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg text-sm text-red-700';
      statusEl.textContent = 'Error: ' + err.message;
    } finally {
      runBtn.disabled = false;
      spinner.classList.add('hidden');
    }
  });

  document.getElementById('sa-clear').addEventListener('click', () => {
    inputEl.value = '';
    resultEl.classList.add('hidden');
  });
</script>
